    "department": "PCG x International",
    "description": "Introduction\n\nOur international team is expanding the Sales department with talented Market Developers experienced in helping companies grow their client base. If you are an experienced Market Developer with a proven sales track record in selling services, rate yourself high on communication skills and know your way around clients, keep reading!\n\nPrimary Responsibilities\n\n - Develop a strong understanding of PCG’s business and well-defined service portfolio in order to turn leads to new sales\n\n - Promote and represent PCG’s services\n\n - Prospect and qualify new sales leads following a defined sales process\n\n - Schedule meetings and presentations with prospects\n\n - Create, plan, and deliver presentations on company services\n\n - Daily tracking of all sales activities in company CRM system\n\n - Maintain a well-developed pipeline of prospects\n\n - Develop strong, ongoing relationships with prospects\n\n - Prepare, send and follow up on contracts sent based on company templates\n\n - Collaborate closely with Solutions Architects when proposing solutions to prospects\n\n - Negotiate contract terms with clients and communicate with stakeholders\n\n - Ability and willingness to travel for meetings with prospective and existing clients\n\n - Coordinate with other team members and departments to optimize the sales effort\n\n - Meet or exceed monthly KPIs\n\n - Create weekly reports for management\n\n - Regularly collecting and analyzing the insights from the sales activities and providing feedback to the management team\n\nQualifications\n\n - Bachelor's degree in Business, Marketing, Communications, or a related field\n\n - 5+ years of sales experience\n\n - Native or bilingual Swedish speaker\n\n - Fluency in English is a must\n\n - Tech-savvy with a good understanding of IT concepts\n\n - Working experience in the Tech industry or technical background\n\n - Proven ability to meet and exceed sales quotas\n\n - Proven track record of successfully managing customer relationships\n\n - Excellent interpersonal skills\n\n - Highly self-motivated and achievement oriented\n\n - Strong verbal and written communication and presentation skills\n\n - Proficient in Microsoft Office\n\n - Working knowledge of CRM systems\n\nDesired Skills\n\n - Self-confident\n\n - Customer service oriented\n\n - Upbeat, creative and highly engaged\n\n - Great organizational skills\n\n - Strong interest in cloud services\n\n - Attention to detail, great listening and speaking skills\n\n - Innovative – prefers working in unconventional ways or on tasks that require creativity\n\n - Intermediate knowledge of a few other European languages\n\nWe Offer\n\n - Competitive compensation\n\n - Premium equipment\n\n - 20+ paid vacation days\n\n - Personalised career path\n\n - An international, friendly and collaborative environment\n\n - Hybrid work model\n\n - Possibility for learning and self-realisation\n\n - Flat hierarchy and inclusive environment\n\nAbout PCG\n\nPublic Cloud Group (PCG) supports companies in their digital transformation through the use of public cloud solutions.\n\nWith a product portfolio designed to accompany organisations of all sizes in their cloud journey and competence that is a synonym for highly qualified staff that clients and partners like to work with, PCG is positioned as a reliable and trustworthy partner for the hyperscalers, relevant and with repeatedly validated competence and credibility.\n\nWe have the highest partnership status with the three relevant hyperscalers: Amazon Web Services (AWS), Google, and Microsoft. As experienced providers, we advise our customers independently with cloud implementation, application development, and managed services.",
